description:
1. Just fine Sushi;
2. Uninformed wait-staff;
3. Crowded dining room;
4. An atmosphere so noisy that you can't hear even your own thoughts, much less the conversation from your dinner partner;
5. And a tab for two that exceeded $500.

Which one of these things is not like the others?

The sushi was good.  Depending on your standards, you might even say it was very good.  But it was certainly not the best I've had in the Bay Area (as I was led to expect).  The waiter was uninformed even of the types of sushi he was serving (forget about the sake/wine list).  And while the views were beautiful and the decor tasteful, the atmosphere was ruined by tables crammed in next to each other -- our romantic dinner for two felt like it was taking place at a communal table for 50.  And did I mention that it was noisy?  Even the dining room provided little escape from the din of conversation mixed with house music emanating from the bar.  

All of that would make for a perfectly average sushi experience in the Bay Area, as I can think of several places that either fit or come close to the above description . . . except for the price.

We went into it fully expecting an expensive dinner -- we ordered the omakase and enjoyed a very good (if overpriced) bottle of wine.  But we were looking for an experience to match the tab.

//------------------------------DON'T EAT HERE----------------------------------//

I have never given a review on yelp but I felt compelled to write about the horrendous experience I had here. After waiting 30 minutes for my table when the hostess said 10 I was finally sat to enjoy the most disgusting meal ever. First off, their rolls were badly mad more like my 5 year old cousin made them and then I found a tiny little worm in my ankimo. For those of you who don' t know ankimo is monkfish liver. I m sorry but if I am paying 4 times what the food is worth I expect my food to be insect free. Oh, and I could have gotten better service at Macdonalds where at least they give your food with a smile. Save your money and go to Yoshis  or Tsunami. Trust me you won't regret it.
